cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Vacant — a responsibility-layer residency form for AI agents"
message: "If you use Vacant in academic or industrial work, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Hsu
    given-names: Cosmo
    alias: cosmopig
    email: cosmo20050801@gmail.com
abstract: >-
  Vacant is a stand-alone "responsibility layer" that sits on top of
  A2A and MCP. An agent that adopts the vacant residency form gains
  Ed25519 identity, an append-only signed logbook (history), a
  five-dimensional Beta-posterior reputation per substrate, with
  STYLO-distance discount and same-controller / same-substrate /
  same-stylo detection (cost-raising, not preventing). The 14-week MVP
  ships four reference scenarios and one adversarial scenario,
  asserted in CI against a frozen-fixture integration suite.
keywords:
  - multi-agent
  - mcp
  - a2a
  - reputation
  - identity
  - responsibility-layer
  - llm
  - claude
